# ORIG TITLE    People in Tallin get a free ride . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Tallinn has become the first European capital to offer free public transport across its bus and tram network. Officials say it is an attempt to make the Estonian capital one of the greenest in Europe and the decision was backed by the majority of citizens in a referendum last year. But critics have said the move is politically motivated and a poor use of public funds. 
